      "note": "Sc., \"and he ought to be an example for you as regards your behaviour towards one another\", i.e., he would not accept rashly a hearsay tale affecting the honour of third persons, but would either refuse to listen to it altogether or, should a clarification become necessary in the interests of the community, would insist on ascertaining the truth objectively."
